  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Successful Treatment of Maternal Listeria Monocytogenes Bacteremia in the First Trimester of
      Pregnancy
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      A 34-year-old nulliparous woman with 11 gestational weeks with flu-like illness was proved to
      be infection by Listeria monocytogenes, and then treated by intravenous ampicillin 2 g every
      4 hours for 3 weeks. A healthy unaffected male baby was delivered at 41 weeks' gestation.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
